    category: 'insurance',
  },
  {
    question: 'What if you scratch my floors or damage the walls?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Painless Removals uses floor runners and door protectors as standard on every move. If damage does occur, our public liability insurance covers it.<br><br>We lay protective runners on all floors before we start moving anything. Door frames get padded protectors on both sides. We take "before" photos of any existing damage so there are no disputes. If something does get marked, tell the team on the day — most scuffs can be sorted immediately.`,
    category: 'insurance',
  },
  {
    question: "I've got a really expensive painting — what happens if it's damaged?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Declare any individual item worth over £2,000 to Painless Removals before the move. We can arrange additional cover.<br><br>Our standard Goods in Transit policy covers up to £15,000 per van, but high-value individual items (artwork, antiques, jewellery, instruments) need to be declared in writing. Once declared, we can increase coverage through our insurer. We'll also use specialist packing — acid-free tissue, custom picture crates, and padded blankets — to give it the best possible protection.`,
    category: 'insurance',
  },
  {
    question: 'How do I make a claim if something goes wrong?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Call your Move Manager, photograph the damage, and we'll handle it directly. No third parties, no runaround.<br><br>Painless Removals manages all claims in-house. Photograph the damage, note which item and where it was in the van, and contact your Move Manager within 7 days. Most claims are resolved quickly. We've been in business since 1978 because we deal with problems honestly — not because we never have any.`,
    category: 'insurance',
  },
  {
    question: "What's the difference between your insurance and a man-and-van's?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Painless Removals carries £15,000 Goods in Transit insurance per van. Most man-and-van services carry zero.<br><br>Without Goods in Transit insurance, if your belongings are damaged during the move, you have no recourse. You'd need to make a claim on your own home contents insurance — if it even covers removals. With Painless Removals, you're covered from the moment we pick up your first box to the moment we place the last one. Being Move Assured accredited means we're held accountable by an independent body too.`,
    category: 'insurance',
  },

  // ===== 7. Storage & In-Between Moves =====
  {
    question: "My new place isn't ready yet — what do I do?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Painless Removals loads your belongings, takes them to secure storage, and delivers them to your new home when it's ready. One team, no double handling.<br><br>This is more common than you'd think — especially with chain moves where completion dates slip. We load your belongings onto the van, transport them to our secure <a href="/storage-service/">storage facility</a>, and keep them safe until your new property is ready. When the time comes, the same team delivers everything. You avoid paying for two separate collections.`,
    category: 'storage',
  },
  {
    question: "Can I get to my stuff while it's in storage?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes — you can access your stored belongings by arrangement with Painless Removals.<br><br>Our <a href="/storage-service/">storage page</a> has full details on access, security, and how to book a visit.`,
    category: 'storage',
  },
  {
    question: "How much does storage cost if I'm already using you for the move?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Painless Removals customers get 50% off storage for the first 2 months.<br><br>Unit sizes and full pricing are on our <a href="/storage-service/">storage service page</a>. Starting from around £41 per month for a 25 sq ft unit, up to £157 per month for 200+ sq ft. The 50% discount applies to the first 2 months when combined with a removal booking.`,
    category: 'storage',
  },
  {
    question: "Can you store just a few things — like one room's worth?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes — Painless Removals offers flexible storage unit sizes, starting from just 25 sq ft.<br><br>You don't need to fill a whole container. We'll help you choose the right size during your <a href="/free-home-survey/">survey</a>. See all unit sizes and pricing on our <a href="/storage-service/">storage page</a>.`,
    category: 'storage',
  },
  {
    question: 'What if I end up needing storage longer than I planned?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> No problem. Painless Removals storage is month-to-month with no long-term contracts.<br><br>Life doesn't always go to plan — renovations overrun, chains collapse, plans change. You can keep your belongings in storage for as long as you need. Just let us know roughly when you'd like delivery, and we'll schedule it. There's no penalty for extending.`,
    category: 'storage',
  },

  // ===== 8. About Painless Removals =====
  {
    question: 'How long have you actually been doing this?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Painless Removals has been moving people in and around Bristol since 1978 — that's 47 years and counting.<br><br>The company was founded by Steve, a Bristol musician who started moving his bandmates between gigs and flats. It's grown a bit since then. Today, Painless Removals is led by Director <a href="/about/jay-newton/">Jay Newton</a>, who has personally overseen more than 2,000 completed moves. We're still based in Bristol, still independent, and still doing things properly.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
  {
    question: 'Will I deal with the same person the whole way through?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes. Jay personally conducts every home survey, and once you're booked your dedicated Move Manager takes over — planning the logistics, confirming the details, and overseeing the team on the day.<br><br>One person who already knows your move, so you never have to repeat yourself. It's one of the main reasons our customers rate us ${siteConfig.company.rating.value} out of 5.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
  {
    question: "Who's Jay Newton?",
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> <a href="/about/jay-newton/">Jay Newton</a> is the Director of Painless Removals. He's hands-on, personally trains the team, and has overseen more than 2,000 completed moves.<br><br>Jay took over the running of Painless Removals and has maintained the company's reputation for personal, no-nonsense service. He still gets involved in complex moves and is available to speak to customers directly. You can reach Jay through our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a> or by calling ${siteConfig.company.contact.phone}.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
  {
    question: 'Are your reviews real?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes — all ${siteConfig.company.rating.count} of them. Painless Removals has a ${siteConfig.company.rating.value} average star rating on Google, and every review is from a verified customer.<br><br>We don't buy reviews, incentivise them, or cherry-pick the good ones. After every move, we simply ask customers if they'd mind leaving honest feedback. The results speak for themselves. You can read them all on <a href="/reviews/">our reviews page</a> or directly on our <a href="https://g.page/painlessremovals" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Business profile</a>.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you do removals outside Bristol?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes — Painless Removals covers the whole of the UK. We regularly move customers from Bristol to London, Cardiff, Manchester, Edinburgh, and everywhere in between.<br><br>Bristol's location on the M4 and M5 corridors makes us well-placed for moves in any direction. The same dedicated team handles your entire move from start to finish — we never subcontract. Routes passing through or near Bristol are where we're most competitive on price, but we'll quote for any UK destination.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
  {
    question: 'Do you cover Portishead, Clevedon, Bath, and Weston?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Yes — Painless Removals covers all of these areas and more across the South West.<br><br>We serve <a href="/removals-portishead/">Portishead</a>, <a href="/removals-clevedon/">Clevedon</a>, <a href="/removals-bath/">Bath</a>, <a href="/removals-weston-super-mare/">Weston-super-Mare</a>, <a href="/removals-keynsham/">Keynsham</a>, <a href="/removals-yate/">Yate</a>, <a href="/removals-thornbury/">Thornbury</a>, <a href="/removals-nailsea/">Nailsea</a>, <a href="/removals-chepstow/">Chepstow</a>, and every neighbourhood in Bristol from <a href="/removals-bristol/clifton/">Clifton</a> to <a href="/removals-bristol/fishponds/">Fishponds</a>. See our complete <a href="/areas/">area coverage page</a> for the full list.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
  {
    question: 'What happens to all the cardboard and packing waste?',
    answer: `<strong>Short answer:</strong> Painless Removals collects and recycles used packing materials. If you used our packing service, collection is free.<br><br>Once you've finished unpacking, give us a call and we'll arrange a convenient time to collect boxes, paper, and bubble wrap. We reuse sturdy boxes where possible and recycle the rest. We're working to reduce plastic packaging by switching to paper-based alternatives wherever they offer equivalent protection. If you packed yourself, we can still collect — just ask.`,
    category: 'about-us',
  },
];

// Helper: strip HTML for schema plain text
function stripHtml(html: string): string {
  return html.replace(/<[^>]*>/g, '').replace(/\s+/g, ' ').trim();
}

// Build schemas
const domain = siteConfig.brand.domain;

const webPageSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "WebPage",
  "name": pageTitle,
  "description": pageDescription,
  "url": `${domain}/faq`,
  "isPartOf": {
    "@type": "WebSite",
    "name": siteConfig.brand.name,
    "url": domain,
  },
  "mainEntity": {
    "@type": "MovingCompany",
    "@id": `${domain}/#business`,
  },
};

const pageSchema = [faqPage(faqs.map(f => ({ question: f.question, answer: stripHtml(f.answer) }))), breadcrumbs([
  { name: "Home", path: "/" },
  { name: "FAQ" },
]), webPageSchema];
---

<Layout title={pageTitle} description={pageDescription} schema={pageSchema}>

  <!-- ============================================
       HERO — Compact, centered
  ============================================ -->
  <section class="gradient-hero py-6 lg:py-14">
    <div class="container-wide text-center">
      <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
      <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="mb-6">
        <ol class="flex items-center justify-center gap-2 text-sm text-warm-gray">
          <li><a href="/" class="hover:text-primary-600 transition-colors no-underline">Home</a></li>
          <li><span class="text-gray-400">/</span></li>
          <li class="text-primary-600 font-medium">FAQ</li>
        </ol>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl lg:text-4xl xl:text-5xl font-bold mb-4">
        Got Questions About Moving?<br class="hidden sm:block" /> <span class="text-secondary-500">We've Got Answers.</span>
